## Edge Cases and Error Handling

- **Performance**: Julia set rendering requires an iterative loop in the fragment shader. The maximum number of iterations must be strictly capped (e.g., 8 to 16 max) to prevent GPU stalling and maintain the 60 FPS constraint (SAFETY RAIL #1).
- **Missing Depth**: Fallback gracefully (e.g. use a default UV radius or bypass) to avoid divide-by-zero or static rendering (SAFETY RAIL #7).
- **Temporal Feedback**: Includes a `texPrev` feedback loop. Ping-pong FBOs MUST be explicitly deleted on unload (SAFETY RAIL #8).

